This paper focuses on designing routing protocols for Mobile Ad-Hoc Networks (MANETs) with the goal of increasing network lifetime by reducing energy consumption. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper proposes a multi-metric routing scheme that takes into consideration multiple layer parameters, such as MAC queue utilization, node degree, and residual energy, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also evaluates the proposed protocol modifications through simulations, which could place it in cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
